<br>
It was a tone those of the temple knew well. &quot;When she is icy, or raging,&quot; the novices would whisper &quot;You have a chance. When she becomes calm, and her voice is reasonable ...then pray to Thule for all you are worth... &quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;How nice of you to come and see me. Do have a seat?&quot;<br>
<br>
She watched, as the young shadowknight continued to stand before her. Her nostrils flared a little, seeking the telltale scent of fear. <br>
<br>
&quot;This came for me High Priestess.  I brought it to you right away&quot;  He handed her the letter.<br>
<br>
Littany scanned the contents once, then slowing re-read it again. She looked up at D'Ron Karr, and a faint smile grew in the edges of her eyes. It was not, to be honest, a very nice smile.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah, the bard persists.  Meledi is not one to admit that she is helpless in a situation, she has this obsessive, urgent need to take action.  How....quaint. She seeks to see Tanare once more.  This is amusing.&quot; Littany's voice took on a certain edge.  &quot;Given that I can hardly get anyone within the temple to tolerate being in the room with that ranger long enough to maintain a proper guard. I have never had so many priests have urgent need to take leave, so many novices with sudden illnesses, so many priestesses walking around with strained looks on their faces.  I have even prayed to Lord Cazic to ask it the sacrifice is suitable, to send a sign... and nothing.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; By all means D'Ron Karr, arrange to have Meledi come to visit our humble temple - to be with Tanare.  Let her think you do this without my knowledge out of the ..&quot; a faint scorn creeps into her voice &quot; goodness of your heart or softness of you head, I care not which.&quot;<br>
<br>
Littany waved a hand in dismissal, and as D'Ron Karr left the room he heard a small laugh from the High Priestess. The very air seemed to grow darker and chill at the sound.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
