into the Paineel city yard, judged her distance <br>
away from the skeleton guards, Heridion and<br>
Mebuknar, of whom she was very afraid, and<br>
snuck back to the entrance to the Warrens. <br>
Heridion himself (or itself?) had struck her<br>
quite a blow the other day, which left her trembling.<br>
<br>
&quot;I, Aurwena Kondratieva, promise to try and save<br>
Tanare, whatever the cost may be,&quot; she whispered<br>
to the silence of the meditative pool. Her Camouflage,<br>
given to her by the other Human Ranger, had worn<br>
off, and she was plotting her next move. However,<br>
Zek had not given her a sign of what that was to<br>
be. Neither had Veeshan or Zeboxurok, for that matter.<br>
<br>
Suddenly, a vision flashed before her eyes: A lovely<br>
Erudite woman, kneeling before an altar in prayer<br>
or meditation, suddenly raised her head and sniffed<br>
the air. Aurwena suspected that what the lady was<br>
smelling was fear--Aurwena's own fear. The young<br>
Ranger swallowed hard. Did the Erudite know she<br>
was in Paineel? Would she send the skeletons to<br>
kill her on sight? Aurwena tried to hide, but to no<br>
avail. She would have to either enter the Warrens<br>
or the city, and neither option seemed agreeable.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=olmembar>OlmEmbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/17/03 10:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1> To Meledi Weaver<br>
League of Honor<br>
Darian's Bar<br>
Shadowhaven<br>
<br>
Dear Meledi<br>
<br>
I am sorry to hear that your talks with High Priestess Littany D'Thule did not work out.   It is unfortunate that this has to be, had the temple not burned down along with the city there would have been no need for the dedication of a new temple.   <br>
<br>
I am indeed fond of Tanare, as I belive you suspect,  and have grown to like her even more as time passes by.  <br>
She is being housed comfortably, given appropriate food and drink, and is well guarded.  No harm will come to her, at least until the Cereamony of Moondark.<br>
<br>
For now, she waits happily for her new ceramonial robe to be trailored for her, and also with her own sewing.<br>
I have brought her some sewing supplies and she has begun to actually attain some skill in the art of tailoring herself.<br>
<br>
I have thought long and hard upon your request.  It does not seem to be an unreasonable one.<br>
Tanare, I am sure would be most happy to see you, and to show you her new skills as well.  She remains unaware of her situation, though I have tried to explain it to her.  For now, we simply try to keep her happy. <br>
  <br>
I will make the necessary arrangements that will allow me to safely escort you to her, but we will have to do so within a tight timeframe.   You will need to come alone and unarmed.  <br>
I will be waiting for you at the Pillar of Knowledge that is just outside the tunnel leading to Paineel, tomarrow at four PM, Paineel time.  That is slightly before I assume my guard duty, and my own presence in the area will not be suspected.   You will just need to follow me and remain invisable.<br>
<br>
Yours also, <br>
D'Ron Karr<br>
Apprentice guardian<br>
<br>
