<br>
She had known that it would be a trap, and come unarmed fully expecting it. D'Ron Karr had met her outside Paineel.  Again, it was a shock to think that a shadowknight could look so much like a Paladin. But then and again, appearances could be deceptive. Well she knew this. D'Ron Karr had seemed only slightly surprised as she had changed - perhaps he thought that it was a spell or enchantment.<br>
<br>
It was the first time in over a year that she had taken off her mask and revealed her true heritage to any. Gray knew, it was partly this that had allowed their friendship. And of course her half sister Kyrial had always known the truth, although their human mother would never speak of the details. But the skin of a Teir Dal was accepted in Paineel, and so for a short while she had show the only legacy her father had left her... <br>
<br>
D'Ron Karr then in his strangely gracious way escorted her inside.  The click of the bolt behind her however was the tell tale, he still served the Priestess of Thule. <br>
<br>
She knew the League would have thought this act of hers rash, and stopped her if they had realized her intent. But, she had to do something - and sometimes desperate plans could work.<br>
<br>
She put her mask back on, realizing however that she would alarm Tanare if she did not look as always. The child was sleeping, her face innocent ... her lips moving only slightly as she talked inside her dreams. A doll cuddled in the crook of her arm, and a few half sewn pelt were strewn around.<br>
<br>
It was time to wake her now.. she leaned over, and gently shook the ranger. <p><img border=0 src="http://www.leagueofhonour.com/images/members/meledi-sig.jpg" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhaxalygen>Rhaxalygen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 338<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/19/03 5:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1> The cell next to Tanare's was chilly and damp, and<br>
Aurwena's heart beat wildly with fear as she realized<br>
what had happened. The Paladin had tricked her. <br>
<br>
He, D'ron Karr, had imprisoned her in a cell next<br>
to Tanare's, shackles and all, instead of letting her<br>
rescue the poor young Ranger she had come to save.<br>
Now Aurwena was a prisoner herself, and she was<br>
afraid. She had never been so uncertain, nor so<br>
ashamed of herself. But she had thought D'ron Karr good!<br>
<br>
The young Wood Elf slipped into an uneasy doze,<br>
hearing the voice of one of the Triad, Veeshan, roar<br>
at her with the impatience of a rabid kobold:<br>
<br>
&quot;You've forgotten my motto already, my dear! Look out<br>
for number one! Even though you don't even have your<br>
Camouflage spell yet, you stole off to Paineel and <br>
attempted to rescue this Ranger you don't even know?<br>
I should think that such foolhardy actions were beyond<br>
your wise mind, but now I know otherwise, Kondratieva!<br>
<br>
Here's the deal: Tanare, this muddle-headed Wood Elf<br>
that's even more naive and stupid than you've been (FAR<br>
more naive and stupid, in my opinion!), is to be sacrificed.<br>
She is to be killed in the name of Cazic-Thule to dedicate<br>
the Temple of Terror to him. Tanare will die soon, unless<br>
this Meledi Weaver, a very sentient Bard, rescues her.<br>
<br>
Do not attempt to rescue Tanare anymore. Get out if you<br>
can! You are pardoned for your rash actions this time, <br>
but Zek and I desire more foresight and patience from<br>
our warriors. Zeboxurok is alarmed at what you've done,<br>
also. See how you've dismayed your new Triad, dear!&quot; <br>
<br>
In her dreams, Aurwena wept, trembling with fear and shame.<br>
<br>
&quot;Listen,&quot; said Veeshan. &quot;You have one more Cloudy Potion<br>
left, that that false Paladin has given to you in order to hide<br>
you from the Heretics of Paineel and the guards. Use it to<br>
your advantage! Escape! Run! Hide, or who knows what <br>
the High Priestess Littany will do with you after Tanare's<br>
dead! That dupe has no future, but you do. Now, flee, my <br>
Kondratieva, before Moondark comes! I'm with you, child!&quot; <br>
<br>
Aurwena awoke with a start, rattling her tight iron chains. <br>
Could she escape, or even reach her last Cloudy Potion?<br>
Fear coursed through her like blood through her arteries,<br>
and the young Ranger was torn between her loyalty to<br>
Tanare and Veeshan's words: &quot;Seek only your own good!&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oligith>Oligith</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/untitled.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf of Many Faces</span><br>  Posts: 740<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/20/03 12:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.leagueofhonour.com/images/members/oligith2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1> Though he dared not show it, the encounter Oligith had with Littany in the main bank of New Tanaan the night before gave the enchanter much to worry about.<br>
<br>
What did Littany mean about Meledi not being missed in the League of Honour?  Had something befallen his Guildmistress as she was attending to her regular duties in the League of Antonican Bards that she had gone out to do this morning?<br>
<br>
Questions buzzed in his mind though his, at that time, erudite face smiled at the Priestess of Fear.  Having devoted so much time to cleansing the planes of Nightmare, Hate, Torment, Decay, and Disease, had he lost sight of the battles needed fighting back home?  These questions needed answers and the Phantasmist knew exactly where to begin.<br>
<br>
Heading to the guildmaster of the Antonican Bards in New Tanaan, Oligith adopted the form of a Lord of Kelethin in all his finery and using an enchantment to improve the guildmaster's feelings towards him, requested to discover where Meledi had been sent that morning.  And to please bring the results found to the enchanter known as Oligith Fandarel in hall above Darian's Bar in Shadowhaven.<br>
<br>
Knowing that would take some time, Oligith next proceeded to Shadowhaven and the Halls of the League of Honour above Darian's Bar to check on the comings and goings of the members of the League.  Memebers were supposed to note when they arrived and went in a book made available for this purpose, but just as the enchanter himself had been lax in doing so, so had the other Legionairres.<br>
<br>
Frustrated after searching for a while for clues in the guildhall, a knock on the door gained the enchanter's attention.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sir?&quot;  a young druid stood at the door to the League Halls wearing a light tunic and sporting a rusty scimatar.  The enchanter sighed and waved the young wood elf in as he plopped down at a table.  Looking down, Oligith noticed he still appeared as a Lord of Kelethin.  With a thought, he dismissed the illusion and said, &quot;What can I do for you young one?&quot;<br>
<br>
The druid, startled but determined, reached into a sack at his waist and retrieved a paper.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sir, I seek to deliver this note to an Oligith Fandarel of the League of Honour on behalf of the League of Antonican Bards.&quot;<br>
<br>
Realizing that this was a new adventurer attempting to earn some monies by serving the bards just as he himself had done all those years ago, the Koada'Dal enchanter grinned and handed over ten platinum for the note to the astonishment of the druid.<br>
<br>
Reading the note, Oligith scowled.  The note read,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>To: Oligith Fandarel<br>
      League of Honour<br>
      Darian's Bar<br>
      Shadowhaven<br>
From: League of Antonican Bards<br>
Re:  Meledi Weaver<br>
<br>
I have been instructed to inform you that Meledi Weaver was not on duty for the League of Antonican Bards this morning and has requested a leave of absense in her duties for an undetermined period of time.<br>
<br>
Yours Truly,<br>
Virtuoso Ciadus<br>
League of Antonican Bards Guildmaster<br>
New Tanaan</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Oligith dismissed the young druid who had already departed with a wave of his hand as he scowled.  He was out of leads...almost.  Littany had taunted him today that Meledi was missing, well then, the first place to look would be where this priestess of Cazic Thule lives.<br>
<br>
Leaving a note where the other Officers of the League of Honour would see it stating where he was going and why, Oligith swept out of the guildhall quickly.<br>
<br>
Destination: Paineel. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.leagueofhonour.com/images/members/oligith.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Sage Koada'dal Phantasmist of the 64th Circle<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>  Elf of Many Faces</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425188">Equipment</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/OgHist.html">Stories</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oligith>Oligith</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/untitled.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/20/03 12:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=olmembar>OlmEmbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/20/03 1:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1> /ooc  (Aurwena, you are forgetting.  D''Ron did NOT give you those cloudy potions, as he did not have any to begin with,  which was why Littany had to give you one of hers.  The potions given you, as mentioned earlier, were done so /ooc wise so you could get your faction up by slaying the Kobolds, and have a potion left to get back in place in case you didnt.  I do not know how to edit these posts, but that part needs to be edited out, (along with thi