<br>
Traveling quickly using the pillars of knowledge, the enchanter arrived at the entrance to Paineel realizing that he didn't have a key to the entrance.  Pondering for a moment, he turned and proceeded to the guards that he remembered seeing near the entrance to the lair of the kobolds of the region.<br>
<br>
The skeletons stood impassively as the now-erudite approached.  Oligith decided to ask Guard Heridion for a key and cast a spell causing Heridion to regard him amiably.  The guard handed over the key without a second thought.<br>
<br>
Cloaking himself in invisibility as he still didn't know the whereabouts of Littany nor her minions, the enchanter entered the Heratic city of Paineel.  Oligith passed by several inhabitants who, to his suprise, had the appearance of just waking instead of heading off to sleep for the day.  Slightly annoyed, the enchanter continued on through the dark passages of Paineel until he found what he was looking for.<br>
<br>
An old dark elf sat alone in a corner.  Dropping the invisibility with a thought, Oligith cast a quick spell on the man and sat down next to him.  Jerith, the old dark elf, glanced at Oligith and smiled, revealing slightly pointed teeth. <br>
<br>
&quot;Yes?  What can Jerith do for you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I need some information, my good friend Jerith.  I seek the whereabouts of a priestess of Cazic Thule known as Littany or perhaps simply where she has taken up residence recently.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh I know of this High Priestess Littany.  She holds high favor with Lord Thule and will be sanctifying the new temple of our Lord during the ceremony of Moondark,&quot; the old dark elf beemed with anticpation.  &quot;Rumor has it that she has a fine lightbringer for the sacrifice.&quot;<br>
<br>
Meledi!  Startled but not daring to show it, Oligith hid his feelings with a cough before forcing a seemingingly delighted smile. <br>
<br>
&quot;That is good news.  Now where might I find the residence of Littany?&quot;<br>
<br>
Under the thrall of the charm, Jerith didn't think it odd that a supposed resident of Paineel would ask such a question, and responded happy to be able to help his best friend, &quot;You'll likely find her in the Tabernacle of Terror.&quot;<br>
<br>
Oligith thanked the old man and glanced around.  Seeing no one near, he broke the charm he had on Jerith who immediately realized what had just happened and lept at the enchanter in fury.  Batting feebly against the powerful runes protecting Oligith, he couldn't prevent the enchanter from casting the sleep spell.  With one more incantation on the old dark elf, Oligith knew Jerith wouldn't remember ever meeting him.<br>
<br>
Renewing the cloak of invisibility, Oligith crept quickly to the Tabernacle of Terror.  Following a servant into the building, the enchanter was very careful to make certain that his presence would not be known to any who might see through his invisibility.  Intent on finding where Meledi might be imprisoned...it had to be Meledi! ....Oligith hunted for another opportunity to find information.  Eventually, he found one.<br>
<br>
A single erudite man was walking down the hallway.  Invisible, Oligith followed him closely all the way into a small room at the end of the hall.  After the man locked the door behind him, Oligith looked around and noticed the room was a lavoritory.  Before he could unfasten his belt, Oligith began casting his spell.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh pardon me,&quot; the man was startled, &quot;I didn't see you in here.  I'll just...&quot;<br>
<br>
Oligith cut him off, &quot; Oh no.  It is I who should apologize.  I forgot to lock the door behind me, but I have finished.  If you'll excuse me....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Dzan Amo,&quot; Dzan helpfully provided in the pause.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes Dzan Amo.  I am most embaressed.  I must have been rushing too fast because it was my turn to bring lunch to the intended sacrifice of the Moondark, and I am late to retrieve it.  What is worse, I don't even know where to take the food after I obtain it!&quot;  Oligith put on the air of being highly distressed.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's all right.  I had to bring her some animal pelts not too long ago and know exactly where to find her.  If you'll just give me a moment, I'll be glad to lead you there,&quot; Dzan said helpfully.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh!  I could never live down the shame of having to be led to her room.  If you could just give me some good directions...&quot;<br>
<br>
Dzan Amo was very helpful and gave very good directions before Oligith put him to sleep in the Lavoritory and wiped his memory of the entire episode.<br>
<br>
Traveling quickly and invisible, the enchanter found the door and listened... <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.leagueofhonour.com/images/members/oligith.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Sage Koada'dal Phantasmist of the 64th Circle<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>  Elf of Many Faces</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425188">Equipment</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/OgHist.html">Stories</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oligith>Oligith</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/untitled.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/20/03 1:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=olmembar>OlmEmbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/21/03 7:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1> D'Ron Karr sat in a darkened corner of the temple, meditating, and deep in prayer. <br>
He had already given prayerful aknowledgement to Cazic Thule, but now concentrated upon the god that he served.<br>
Purging his mind of unneeded thoughts and desires, he began to pull upon the forces of shadow to aid him in his tasks.  <br>
His eyes glowed underneath closed lids,  his muscles bulged and his presence carried a strong flavor of menace which grew as he meditated.  He then opened his eyes and pulled out his spell book, memorizing the spells that he would use and stood up, casting his servent, and then casting upon himself.  <br>
He remorized a couple of more spells then set off to start upon his next tasks, his aura reeking of grimness and the scent of death.  A stray thought flickered in his mind and he almost laughed.  <br>
*Like it is a real challange to terrorize and threaten teenagers....well maybe Tanare, but..certainly he didn't last very long again Baron Drayco the other day.   Littany and her pride over practically, well that was a cleric of Thule for you, no fear....when perhaps there should have been.*<br>
<br>
He nodded to the guard to open the cell, and then stepped in along with two other guards, the guard with the key locking it behind him.   The two guards approached Aurwena and unlocked her manicles, then stood to either side of her.<br>
D'Ron wearing his black armor and the whip on his side, then spoke.<br>
&quot;You will divest yourself of all armor and any weapons still concealed upon yourself.  You may still wear your underpadding for decency's sake. <br>
If you fail to do this, the armor will be forceably  removed off of you and you will be punished.  He let his aura of menace expand upon her as he rested his hand upon the Sarnak War Braid, then unlimbered it and cracked it's tip against the side of the wall next to her face, making her jump a bit.<br>
He watched and smiled grimly as she began to do so, and noted that there was some slight trembling in her movements.  When the task was finished, the manicles were once again locked together, but this time infront of her, and with a chain attached to one of the walls that still allowed her some movement.   The guards then collected up the armor and with the cell door opening once again, headed out with it.<br>
<br>
D'Ron stepped out into the hallway, the door being closed and locked again behind him, and he noted that still yet another new face was peering into the cell that contained Meledi and Tanare.  At this point he paused and addressed the newcomer.<br>
&quot;What ever your chore is Sir, you need to wait, as they have requested their privacy.  And I need to see them again first.  I suggest you wait up by the guard captain, or take a break and return in aproximately  thirty minutes.&quot;<br>
<br>
With anoyance D'Ron noticed that the man did not wear the robes of either the priests or their Acolytes, but Littany was rather short on volunteers, so perhaps others from the city were offering to take turns in tending to Tanare.  He turned and then walked up the hall to go quickly change his armor and make a trip to the local bakery. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=melediweaver>melediweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dirges, a specialty</span><br>  Posts: 463<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/21/03 8:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=56>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1> &quot;Hello Tanare, and no, I am not here for a dress or a party. I am here because you are in danger.&quot;<br>
