<br>
D'Ron returned shorty as he had said he would, to find Tanare still in conversation with her Meledi, a few guards remarking on the curiousity of a strange visitor who had felt the need to enter their halls invisable, apparently forgetting to take it off once entering the city. <br>
   After asking Tanare to follow him, adding that her guardian could keep her place for her, he informed her that they were to go hunting, and that she needed to put her armor back on for the occasion.   It was to give her a break from waiting, andno, as long as he was there, she didn't really need to be attached to the wall.<br>
After he had left, the other guards entered and  carefully &quot;assisted' Meledi with the removal of her armor and musical instrumentation.<br>
<br>
--------------<br>
<br>
<br>
[Fri Nov 21 20:41:24 2003] You have entered an Arena (PvP) area.<br>
<br>
Tanare looks at Dronkarr curiously to see which one of him is here today, thinks its too bad he has the helmet on so she can't see the initial head wound.<br>
<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, '&lt;points to the sleeping meledi&gt; shhh she's like sleeping and stuff cause she;s tired from running here, i was like telling her about everything that happened since i got here then i looked over and she was asleep and stuff &lt;nods&gt;'<br>
You say, 'Greetings My Ladies...&lt;glances over at Meledi&gt;'<br>
You say, 'Oooh....&lt;talks softer&gt;'<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, '&lt;keeps talking with a normal tone of voice&gt; so you like came back after all&gt; i knew evil dronky was lying &lt;nods&gt;'<br>
<br>
Dronkarr lifts an eyebrow.<br>
You say, 'Well, I was given permission by Littany to visit, and even take you out hunting again'<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Killing more bad doggies?'<br>
Tanare is excited about the idea.<br>
Tanare tells you, in Elvish, 'Ok'<br>
<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Ooh look what I made while you were gone &lt;proudly points to the pile of Patchwork Pants she has in the corner&gt;'<br>
You say, 'Ah, very good, you are getting better at it.'<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Though I kept messing up when I was using the drinky stuff like you told me, do you think it made me too smart or something?'<br>
You say, 'And I notice you are out of drink also, we shall have to remedy that.'<br>
<br>
You say, 'Humm, perhaps you need to space the drinks out a bit.'<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Well the walls are still leaking so its not that bad'<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Oh...'<br>
You say, 'They really are more for helping your stamina that anything else'<br>
<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Is that why Littany and her father want a new temple place cause this one leaks all the time?'<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Well mighty and tough rangers don't need any help in that cause we ARE mighty and tough you know &lt;nods&gt;'<br>
You say, 'No actually, because her own temple to her father burned down'<br>
<br>
<br>
You say, 'but you werent born that way, and if you do not exercise, you get weak'<br>
You say, 'Speaking of exercise....'<br>
Dronkarr takes a key out and proceeds to unlock Tanare's manicles.<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Ooh.. does he know about it? I bet someone knocked one of the torches over didn't they? my second cousin did that once and burnt the whole tree down before it got put out...i never saw him again though after everyone yelled at him and stuff...'<br>
<br>
You say, 'Ummm, yes , I guess that might be what caused it.<br>
Tanare smiles proudly at her clever deduction.<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Um won't I lose my place in line though?'<br>
<br>
You say, 'Anyways, since your guardian...Meledi, is here, she can hold your place in line for you until you get back.'<br>
<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Oh ok...she's not going to cut is she? she said she wasn;t here for dresses but maybe she was being sneaky....'<br>
Tanare looks worried at the prospect of losing her place in line after so long.<br>
You say, 'No, now why would your own guardian want to take something from you? '<br>
<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Cuase the dress is REAL cute...of course they haven't even come for a fitting yet...then they might come when i;'m gone and make it in Meledy's size not mine and it'll be like too big and everything!'<br>
You say, 'And besides, she is sleeping right now...and do you wish to get out of shape or remain a mighty and strong ranger?'<br>
<br>
<br>
You say, 'Come out, and lets get you back in your armor. We woulnt be gone all that long....'<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Hey! i AM mighty and tough cause once you like become a ranger it happens magic like<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Oh...alright'<br>
Tanare looks back at meledy to make sure she's not pretending to sleep.<br>
You say, 'Shall we go?'<br>
Tanare says, in Elvish, 'Okays'<br>
You have entered an Arena (PvP) area.<br>
You have entered an Arena (PvP) area.<br>
You say, 'ONe stop for supplies, before we leave the city...'<br>
<br>
<br>
Iva Tersala says 'Welcome to my shop, Dronkarr. You would probably find a Muffin handy.'<br>
Tanare begins to cast a spell.<br>
Tanare's skin sprouts thistles.<br>
You give 1 gold to Iva Tersala.<br>
Iva Tersala tells you, 'That'll be 7 copper per Muffin.'<br>
Tanare's fist bursts into flame.<br>
Iva Tersala tells you, 'That'll be 1 silver 7 copper per Bottle of Kalish.'<br>
Tanare begins to cast a spell.<br>
Gorng Alusnein says 'Welcome to my shop, Dronkarr. You would probably find a Mixxy's Delicacies Vol 1 handy.'<br>
Tanare's skin turns hard as stone.<br>
Tanare's eyes gleam and then go dark.<br>
Tanare begins to cast a spell.<br>
<br>
Taralani Rahnta says 'Welcome to my shop, Dronkarr. You would probably find a Grapes handy.'<br>
Taralani Rahnta tells you, 'That'll be 1 silver 7 copper per Short Beer.'<br>
Taralani Rahnta tells you, 'That'll be 4 silver per Red Wine.'<br>
Taralani Rahnta tells you, 'That'll be 2 silver 2 copper per Grapes.'<br>
You give 4 gold 4 silver to Taralani Rahnta.<br>
Taralani Rahnta tells you, 'That'll be 8 silver 5 copper per Brandy.'<br>
You give 1 platinum 7 gold to Taralani Rahnta.<br>
Taralani Rahnta tells you, 'That'll be 4 silver per White Wine.'<br>
You give 6 gold to Taralani Rahnta.<br>
You have entered Toxxulia Forest. <br>
<br>
You say, 'We take the portal to Freeport, then go through the EC tunnel....'<br>
<br>
The two make their way into the Nothern Desert of Ro, stoping momentarily at the wayfarer's camp before continuing on, leaving the greener areas to trudge out into the sand. <br>
As a gust of hot, dry desert wind swirls the sand around them, Tanare takes offense, swatting at it and trying to smooth her hair back. She begins to comment on it, and only pauses for breath when they finally find the hatch to the underground lair and enter in, the coolness affording a temporary releaf.<br>
